column54: Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC) Fittings are the most commonly used plastic piping material. They are manufactured in various dimensions and sizes and are extensively utilised by SV and underground UG in sewer systems, irrigation, water service lines, drain waste vents, and multiple industries.
column99: Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC) Fittings are the most commonly used plastic piping material. They are manufactured in various dimensions and sizes and are extensively utilised by SV and underground UG in sewer systems, irrigation, water service lines, drain waste vents, and multiple industries.

column54: 110mm and 50mm PVC fittings are essential components in plumbing and drainage systems, designed for different pipe sizes and applications. The larger 110mm fittings, such as elbows (90° and 45°), couplers, tees, reducers, end caps, and access caps, are commonly used in soil, waste, and vent (SWV) systems for residential, commercial, and industrial drainage. These fittings allow for directional changes, pipe extensions, branch connections, size reductions, and system maintenance. On the other hand, 50mm PVC fittings, including elbows, couplers, tees, reducers, end caps, and saddle clamps, are used in smaller-scale systems like residential waste drainage, irrigation, and vent piping. They serve similar functions but on a smaller scale, providing flexibility for pipe routing, connections, and system termination. Both sizes of PVC fittings are valued for their durability, corrosion resistance, and ease of installation, making them integral to a wide range of piping systems.

The 110mm 45° Rodding Eye Round is an essential component for efficient maintenance of drainage systems. Designed to provide convenient access to underground pipes, this fitting enables easy clearing of blockages and regular inspection, ensuring optimal system performance. The 45° angle and round design allow for straightforward rodding and smooth operation, even in tight spaces.

Crafted from high-quality materials, this rodding eye offers durability and long-term reliability for both residential and commercial applications. Its robust construction is resistant to wear and ensures a secure fit with compatible drainage systems, making it an indispensable addition to any professional or DIY drainage project.

Choose the 110mm 45° Rodding Eye Round for a practical and dependable solution to drainage access and maintenance. Enhance the longevity and functionality of your drainage network with this high-performance fitting.

column54:
The 110mm 90° Long Radius Bend SV Plain is designed to provide a smooth and efficient 90-degree directional change in soil and vent systems. Its long radius design ensures minimal flow disruption, reducing pressure loss and allowing for a more efficient system performance. This fitting is ideal for applications that require a gradual, controlled bend to maintain optimal flow dynamics within the pipework.

Constructed from high-quality, durable materials, this bend is built to withstand the rigors of both residential and commercial installations. The plain ends ensure easy compatibility with standard fittings, allowing for quick and secure installation.

Choose the 110mm 90° Long Radius Bend SV Plain for a dependable solution to pipework direction changes, ensuring the long-term reliability and efficiency of your drainage or venting system.

The 110mm 90° Long Radius Bend UG Plain is designed to provide a reliable 90-degree directional change for underground drainage systems. Its long-radius design minimizes flow resistance, ensuring smooth and efficient water or waste management. The gradual bend allows for optimal fluid movement, reducing the risk of blockages or strain on the system, making it ideal for underground installations.

Crafted from high-quality materials, this bend is built to endure the challenges of underground environments, offering long-lasting durability and strength. The plain ends allow for compatibility with standard underground pipe fittings, ensuring easy installation and a secure connection.

For reliable and efficient underground drainage, the 110mm 90° Long Radius Bend UG Plain is a professional-grade solution that guarantees performance and durability in the most demanding conditions.

110mm 90° Tee Junction SV Plain – Reliable and Durable Branching Solution for Soil and Vent Systems

The 110mm 90° Tee Junction SV Plain is designed to provide an efficient and reliable 90-degree branching solution in soil and vent systems. This fitting allows for the seamless addition of a new branch to an existing pipe network while ensuring minimal flow disruption. Its robust construction and plain ends provide easy compatibility with standard fittings, ensuring a secure and straightforward installation.

Made from high-quality materials, this tee junction offers durability and long-lasting performance, suitable for both residential and commercial applications. Its precision design ensures a smooth transition, maintaining optimal system performance and reducing the risk of blockages or flow restrictions.

For a dependable and cost-effective branching solution in your soil and vent system, the 110mm 90° Tee Junction SV Plain is an ideal choice for achieving efficient, professional-grade results.

column54: 110mm and 50mm PVC fittings are essential components in plumbing and drainage systems, designed for different pipe sizes and applications. The larger 110mm fittings, such as elbows (90° and 45°), couplers, tees, reducers, end caps, and access caps, are commonly used in soil, waste, and vent (SWV) systems for residential, commercial, and industrial drainage. These fittings allow for directional changes, pipe extensions, branch connections, size reductions, and system maintenance. On the other hand, 50mm PVC fittings, including elbows, couplers, tees, reducers, end caps, and saddle clamps, are used in smaller-scale systems like residential waste drainage, irrigation, and vent piping. They serve similar functions but on a smaller scale, providing flexibility for pipe routing, connections, and system termination. Both sizes of PVC fittings are valued for their durability, corrosion resistance, and ease of installation, making them integral to a wide range of piping systems.

column54:
1. Durability: HDPE pipes are highly resistant to wear, abrasion, and impact, making them suitable for harsh environments.
  2. Flexibility: They are flexible and can be easily bent, which reduces the need for fittings and joints.
  3. Corrosion Resistance: HDPE pipes are immune to corrosion from chemicals, salts, and acids, ensuring long-term reliability.
  4. Leak-Free Joints: The pipes can be joined by heat fusion, resulting in a leak-proof joint that is as strong as the pipe itself.
  5. Lightweight: Easier to handle and install compared to traditional materials like steel or concrete.

Applications:

  • Water Supply: Used in municipal, industrial, and rural water supply systems.
  • Irrigation: Commonly used in agricultural irrigation systems.
  • Sewage and Drainage: Effective in transporting sewage and drainage water due to its resistance to corrosion.
  • Gas Distribution: Suitable for transporting natural gas and other gases.
  • Industrial Applications: Used in chemical processing, mining, and other industries where pipelines are exposed to harsh chemicals.

Dimensions and Sizes:

  • HDPE pipes are available in various diameters and lengths, tailored to specific applications.
  • The thickness of the pipe walls can vary depending on the pressure rating (Class 10 in this case) and the specific requirements of the application.

Compliance and Standards:

  • For HDPE Class 10:
    • Pressure Rating: The pipe can handle a pressure of up to 10 bars (1 bar = 14.5 psi), meaning it's suitable for applications that require up to 10 bars of pressure.
    • Applications: Class 10 HDPE pipes are often used in water supply systems, irrigation, and in some cases, gas distribution, depending on regional standards.

Advantages:

  • Long service life, often exceeding 50 years.
  • Cost-effective due to lower installation costs and reduced maintenance.
  • Environmentally friendly, as HDPE is recyclable and has a lower carbon footprint compared to other materials.

Installation:

  • Can be installed using trenchless technology, reducing the need for extensive digging.
  • Suitable for above-ground, underground, and subaqueous installations.

column54:
Caivil Just For Kids Relaxer and Neutralising Shampoo Fine Hair 225ml + 30ml is a no-lye conditioning relaxer and neutralising shampoo that gently relaxes your child’s fine hair and soothes their scalp.

Caivil Just for Kids Conditioning & Shampoo 255ml
No-Lye Conditioning Relaxer: A low irritation, no mix, gentle relaxer for sensitive scalps and fine hair. 225 ml. Neutralising Shampoo: With colour signal. 30 ml.

Usage instructions:
Directions: For best results, carefully follow intrusions. It is important to first analyse hair in order to choose the correct relaxer strength for your daughter's hair. Always wear gloves while relaxing the hair. Part hair into 4 sections. Apply petroleum jelly as a barrier for the scalp, hairline, ears and nape area before relaxing. Ensure that the relaxer does not touch the scalp. Generously apply the relaxer in sections starting from the crown moving down in a clockwise direction finishing off at the hairline. Smooth hair with the back of the comb. Allow processing between 10 to 15 minutes. Rinse hair thoroughly with lukewarm water, ensuring that all traces of the relaxer are removed. Shampoo hair with Just For Kids neutralising shampoo. Rinse well and repeat shampoo until lather is white and water runs clear. Apply a generous amount of conditioner on the hair and massage through, spreading it evenly. Leave for 5-10 minutes, comb through with a wide-toothed comb to detangle knots. Rinse off and dry. Oil the scalp with Just For Kids hair food and moisturise hair with Just For Kids pink oil moisturiser lotion and style as desired.

A red and black extension cord for a lawn mower is a product designed for outdoor use with a lawn mower or other power tools. While the specific brand and features may vary, here's a general description:

General Description:

  • Color: The most prominent feature is the color, which is a combination of red and black. This is often a safety feature, as bright colors like red make the cord highly visible in grass and foliage, helping to prevent accidental cutting with the mower.
  • Purpose: This cord is specifically intended for use with electric lawnmowers, trimmers, leaf blowers, and other garden tools. It's built to withstand the rigors of outdoor environments.
  • Heavy-Duty Construction: A key characteristic of a lawn mower extension cord is its "heavy-duty" nature. This means it has a thicker cable gauge (e.g., 12 or 14 AWG) to safely handle the high power draw of a lawnmower, preventing voltage drop and overheating. It also typically has a durable, weather-resistant outer jacket to protect against abrasion, moisture, and sunlight.
  • Length: These cords come in various lengths, such as 15m, 20m, 25m, or 30m, to accommodate different lawn sizes. It's important to choose a cord that is long enough for your needs but not excessively long, as a longer cord can lead to a greater voltage drop and reduce the mower's performance.
  • Electrical Specifications: The cord is designed to be used with standard domestic voltage (e.g., 220V in South Africa) and is rated for a specific amperage (e.g., 10A, 15A).
  • Connectors: The cord will have a standard electrical plug on one end to connect to a power outlet and a socket on the other end to connect to the lawn mower's power cord.

In summary, a red and black lawn mower extension cord is a high-visibility, heavy-duty electrical cable built to safely and reliably power outdoor garden tools over an extended distance.

column54:
Start fresh – For maximum all-day protection, make sure your underarms are clean and dry before applying roll-on. If your roll-on contains antiperspirant, apply it the night before. Night-time application gives the antiperspirant time to soak into your skin’s sweat ducts and helps protect you from perspiring the next day.

Towel off – Make sure your underarms are completely dry before you apply roll-on. Your skin’s sweat glands can absorb the antiperspirant better when applied to dry skin.

Shake well – Give your roll-on a good shake to make sure the active ingredients coat the ball correctly.

Apply evenly – Swipe the ball back and forth until you’ve covered the surface of your underarm with a thin layer of roll-on. Usually, three or four strokes are just right for great coverage.

Air dry – Give your underarms a few seconds to dry before you get dressed. This extra step helps ensure that the product absorbs correctly. Always give your roll-on time to dry on your skin before you do anything active that may cause you to perspire.
